{
  "id": 5151468306956288,
  "name": "Interoperable pointerrawupdate events exposed only in secure contexts",
  "summary": "The PointerEvents spec restricted pointerrawupdate to secure contexts in 2020, hiding both the event firing and the global event listeners from insecure contexts.  Through this feature, Chrome will match the updated spec and become interoperable with other major browsers.",
